# Deprecated Workflows
#
# This file lists GitHub Actions workflows that have been intentionally
# removed from this repository. Do NOT reintroduce these files.
#
# Format:
#   <filename> — <reason>

deploy-single-agent.yml — Removed because per-agent deployment is handled
  by the main deploy.yml workflow. A separate single-agent workflow
  introduced maintenance burden, divergent deploy logic, and risk of
  configuration drift. See issue #132 for details.

release-gate.yml — Merged into ci.yml. The PR-only CI workflow now
  serves as the single required status check (lint + build + test gate).
  Eliminates duplicate jobs that ran identically on both PR and merge.

codeql.yml — Removed. GitHub's built-in Code Security / code scanning
  covers the same ground without a dedicated workflow file.

dependency-review.yml — Removed. Dependabot alerts provide equivalent
  coverage for dependency vulnerability scanning.

project-sync.yml — Removed. Excessive event triggers and unused project
  board created unnecessary Actions minute consumption. Associated scripts
  (project-sync.mjs, project-sync-close.mjs, project-sync-reconcile.mjs,
  wip-cap-check.mjs) and policies (wip-cap-policy.json) also removed.

cost-activity-report.yml — Removed. The underlying script
  (scripts/cost-activity-report.sh) remains available for local use.

sync-runtime-issues.yml — Removed. The cron was already disabled. The
  underlying script remains available for local use. Associated policy
  (internal-issue-sync-policy.json) also removed.
